{"altmetric_id":484470,"counts":{"readers":{"mendeley":890,"citeulike":4,"connotea":0},"facebook":{"unique_users_count":1,"unique_users":["115755955105095"],"posts_count":1},"blogs":{"unique_users_count":3,"unique_users":[1260,133,53212],"posts_count":4},"total":{"posts_count":31},"f1000":{"unique_users_count":1,"unique_users":["F1000Prime"],"posts_count":1},"twitter":{"unique_users_count":23,"unique_users":["cbjones1943","provincedr","WomanInScience","Just4Scientists","Poshita_P","K_Miyamichi","closebys","AssoMPS","symphonicworks","WiringTheBrain","psychopium","Recallyou","brainteresting","prerana123","okumakito","timetit","school_money","lihsianghsu","bf4tbrainy","shinycj","umadosikirin","Neurotweeps","susivak"],"posts_count":25}},"selected_quotes":["Ofcourse, this was only a tiny drop in the ocean! Letzkus et al., knocked it out of the park with their work!","L'Inserm d\u00e9couvre de l\u2019\u00e9motion dans le cortex (+ )","Layer 1 interneurons disinhibit pyramidal cells by inhibiting PV+ interneurons, mediating learning","From neurons to neuronal circuits. A disinhibitory microcircuit for associative fear learning in the auditory cortex","Reading and understanding this paper really drove home the point of having circuit motifs that can modulate the output of a sub-field\/region"],"citation":{"abstract":"Learning causes a change in how information is processed by neuronal circuits. Whereas synaptic plasticity, an important cellular mechanism, has been studied in great detail, we know much less about how learning is implemented at the level of neuronal circuits and, in particular, how interactions between distinct types of neurons within local networks contribute to the process of learning. Here we show that acquisition of associative fear memories depends on the recruitment of a disinhibitory microcircuit in the mouse auditory cortex. Fear-conditioning-associated disinhibition in auditory cortex is driven by foot-shock-mediated cholinergic activation of layer 1 interneurons, in turn generating inhibition of layer 2\/3 parvalbumin-positive interneurons. Importantly, pharmacological or optogenetic block of pyramidal neuron disinhibition abolishes fear learning. Together, these data demonstrate that stimulus convergence in the auditory cortex is necessary for associative fear learning to complex tones, define the circuit elements mediating this convergence and suggest that layer-1-mediated disinhibition is an important mechanism underlying learning and information processing in neocortical circuits.","abstract_source":"pubmed","ads_id":"2011Natur.480..331L","altmetric_jid":"4f6fa50a3cf058f610003160","authors":["Johannes J. Letzkus","Steffen B. E. Wolff","Elisabeth M. M. Meyer","Philip Tovote","Julien Courtin","Cyril Herry","Andreas L\u00c3\u00bcthi","Andreas L\u00fcthi"],"doi":"10.1038\/nature10674","endpage":"335","first_seen_on":"2011-12-08T12:21:59+00:00","issns":["0028-0836","1476-4687"],"issue":"7377","journal":"Nature","last_mentioned_on":1506439151,"links":["http:\/\/www.nature.com\/nature\/journal\/vaop\/ncurrent\/full\/nature10674.html","http:\/\/www.nature.com\/nature\/journal\/vaop\/ncurrent\/full\/nature10674.html?WT.ec_id=NATURE-20111208","http:\/\/dx.doi.org\/10.1038\/nature10674","http:\/\/www.nature.com\/nature\/journal\/v480\/n7377\/full\/nature10674.html","http:\/\/www.nature.com\/nature\/journal\/v480\/n7377\/\/abs\/nature10674_ja.html","http:\/\/www.nature.com\/nature\/journal\/v480\/n7377\/full\/nature10674.html?foxtrotcallback=true"],"pmid":"22158104","pubdate":"2011-12-07T00:00:00+00:00","publisher":"Nature Publishing Group","scopus_subjects":["General"],"startpage":"331","subjects":["science"],"title":"A disinhibitory microcircuit for associative fear learning in the auditory cortex.","type":"article","volume":"480","mendeley_url":"http:\/\/www.mendeley.com\/research\/disinhibitory-microcircuit-associative-fear-learning-auditory-cortex"},"altmetric_score":{"score":40.512,"score_history":{"1y":1.35,"6m